                    <div class="faq-question"><div class="faq-icon">Q</div>How long do asphalt shingles last in Michigan?</div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">Architectural shingles typically last 25–30 years in West Michigan. Standard 3-tab shingles run 15–20 years. Michigan's freeze-thaw cycles shorten lifespan on roofs without proper ice and water shield or adequate attic ventilation.</div>
