                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question"><div class="faq-icon">Q</div>Do I need ice and water shield in Grand Rapids?</div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Ice dams form on Grand Rapids rooftops every winter. Ice and water shield at eaves and valleys prevents meltwater from backing up under shingles. Michigan building code requires it, and Kamps installs it on every job.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question"><div class="faq-icon">Q</div>Can I install new shingles over my existing ones?</div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">Technically allowed once under Michigan code, but not recommended. Proper tear-off exposes the deck for inspection, creates a flat nailing surface, and is required for most manufacturer warranties. Shortcuts here typically cost more long-term.</div>
